Displaying images as RAW data (who wants to see base64 encoded images on web site? )  I would always like to see open minded discussions rather than a ton of BS posts... if people choose to invest just because a lost of people said "oh, this is great", "oh, they are nice people", "oh, they are experienced" then this world is doomed No wonder that China put a stop to ICO's until they formalize them...  Edit 1: this just supports my idea that there should be a "body" in charge of formally approving ICO's. i.e. you can't enter the ICO unless you have a workable demo, standardized specification/whitepaper, business model, KYC model for ICO members so if you want to reference that someone is supporting you, advising you, CEO, CBO (chief bullshit office), CXX, whatever then there should be a blockchain trace that they approved this and it is written for all time that they were involved with that ICO and what was their position on that ICO and did they receive any compensation...  As Vitalik said, we should aim to improve what and how can be used in blockchain world...and not just be money driven... this shows me that anything can raise money now days (and let's not kid our-self 6 million dollars, i repeat, 6 MILLION dollars, is a hell lot money to give someone for two web pages with two charts and a login screen)... but again, that is just me...as we can see...6 mil. dollars were paid by people who think this is obviously enough... sad day for humanity....

Author: lugospod
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: Currently the demo isn't showing anything except a couple of graph charts, login,... I went and looked at the project just because McAfee mentioned it...but i honestly think that he only "glazed" at the concept. Also, the concept is based under the assumption that people will give permission to "sether" so that it can access their data...  Also only two team members mention AI experience (one of those two has only 3-4 month experience mentioned on linkedin) and this is is the "core" part of the "product"...  So as far as I see this... people could make money investing in this but not because McAfeee said so but more because every ICO lately makes money for the investors, but I think i'm gonna skip this one.   edit: also, git repository shows "no activity" since they created a github repository a month/two ago... Will this project be open sourced or is the solution proprietary ?? edit 2: did anyone saw the technology landscape or architecture itself? I didn't find any information in the whitepaper. I only assume, based on the linkedin profiles, that it will be oracle based solution... edit 3: did anyone see a list of partners that they plan to do business with? Partners are the one that will "pay" Sether for the core business (there is a pricing model inside the Whitepaper). Maybe I missed that information somewhere on the web site or in the whitepaper... edit 4: it is pretty "brave" statement on their front Web page that they are GDPR compliant - GDPR is much more than just hardware protection...it is a business process. there has to be a Data Protection Officer, users have to accept that their data is gathered, analysed and also people can also ask through which algorithms do you process their data, and a lot lot more...  If anyone has some information, please write...

Author: lugospod
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: At first I wanted to...but now I have a lot of "question marks" flying around  Yeah, it would be better if there was no demo...  if you have a feature that throws "server errors" then you cut it out, because the "public" (that is not in DEV background will not understand this)... Also, as you very eloquently put it, the demo MUST pin point the "selling" points... in the demo I don't care about searches, I don't care about logging in, etc. I want to see how did you "envision" the solution could look like in far future (hopefully not too different )  AI is mentioned on the first page of the web site (part IV). Unfortunately it is not described inside the whitepaper (this is the part that I consider the brain of the operation because anyone can write Web Service calls to Social networks and extract data). Behavior analysis is just shortly described in whitepaper.  Now also, a question pops ups, is this AI opensource or not because that part obviously won't be run on the blockchain (I assume?)...  As I pointed out in my first post, there is no info about possible partnership... if there is no information about that, how did they come up with the pricing sheme? It is described in chapter 7. Prices can only be determined after you analyse the market...  At this time, I would assume that it is "all dev's on deck" time...or in other words "you don't eat, sleep, drink until we launch..." and there is no activity on GIT for a whole month or more... I also didn't find the demo on the git - but this is maybe my fault I lost motivation to go through all of the folders  Until I get more detailed information, this looks like it could have used a couple of months more to prepare... "polish" the demo, create some video, get some "partner" names, fill whitepaper with relevant information because, although I have DEV background, I have no intention of reading each API method that Tweeter, Facebook or any other social network exposes...the only thing I care to see regarding that part is "what will they track"/"which data" - I really don't care using which API method they get it (unless I want to see "why" is something slow) - but currently I am looking it through eyes of an innocent bystander    If I skipped any of your question, please let me know...

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: Dear all,  As we have mentioned before, in the pre-ico period we are focusing on our large investors. And we have quite a few in discussions. There are permanent communication with them, live demos of our technology and so on. This is a business to business platform and a company with a serious approach and a large investment by itself.  We decided to let everybody in the pre-ico without having a cap of minimum investment, because some of our experienced friends in the blockchain ecosystem considered and advised us to democratize the participation, to let everybody benefit in the same conditions as the investors. And we have done this. We are going to have the progressed announced periodically in the crowdsale period as it is normal to be.  If you do not believe in the product or the company than it is better not to invest. Just as an advise, do not invest based on how much money others pretend they raised, or how many people are on BitcoinTalk or Telegram or how many banners some ICOs have or how many influencers.  This is how scams appeared... a lot of money in promotion, fake news, etc. Do your research, study well before investing and take your own decision. The future belongs to the ICOs which are doing real business on blockchain and to the ICOs that have a real company behind, acting like a company, with business experience.  In the end, thank you for supporting us or investing in us or following us. We treasure each and everyone of you.  Kind regards,  Ovidiu Oancea Founder and CEO Sether

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: Social data will be collected using the APIs provided by the social networks. For submitting a user's private credentials to Facebook we use the Intel SGX code and data protection technology. The user is assured that nobody looked at their credentials in the process using the Intel SGX attestation service. More details on this are in the whitepaper.

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: Proof of Action means that one can prove SETHER that they did something on a social network (retweeted, shared a post on facebook, liked a page etc.). SETHER will know if a certain person did a specific action. There is no need to check manually.

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: All altcoins (tokens) have a fixed ETH exchange rate, because it is hard-coded in the smart contract and cannot be changed without altering the contract. What you can do is give bonuses or discounts, but the rate cannot be altered during a crowdsale. After the crowdsale, one could alter the smart contract to change it, but it is NOT recommended. Changing the rate of the token against ETH can dillute investors and could lead to a rapid decrease in the confidence for your project.

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising | Update @17.05.2018   The only blockchain-automated platform for arbitrating advertising campaigns.  Sether acts as a 3-rd party AI regulator between the agency and the client, monitoring and analyzing the performance of an advertising campaign, then distributing the advertising budget according to the registered performance.  How  Sether  works  Any brand can independently contract the services of an online advertising agency, and then run and monitor the entire process through the platform, from the creative process to the actual results of the campaign.  The client and the agency agree to the project deliverables and choose a set of key performance indicators to reflect the performance of the campaign. To correctly compensate campaign efficiency, Sether introduces a set of payment levels for rewarding the performance of the agency according to the results of the campaign and based on the agreed performance indicators.      The Advertiser and the Agency agree to these levels, then the Advertiser loads the funds for the project on the Blockchain, where they are secured by a Smart Contract for the duration or the project. The Blockchain acts as an Escrow account, holding the funds, then automatically distributing them to the Agency, depending on the performance of the campaign.  Follow us on our Social Media Channels:   WEBSITE | TWITTER | FACEBOOK | LINKEDIN |TELEGRAM | YOUTUBE          WHITEPAPER | WEBSITE | TWITTER | FACEBOOK | TELEGRAM | YOUTUBE    SETHER social network data for blockchain businesses  Use Facebook, Twitter, Flickr,  Google Plus, Instagram, LinkedIn, Reddit, Tumblr, YouTube, Pinterest and VKontakte in your blockchain business to create Customer Loyalty, Customer Targeting, Marketing Capaigns, Bounty Campaigns, Political Campaigns and more.  In your smart contracts.   A solid service for the blockchain Sether is the first smart social media data oracle.  Existing data oracles move data between any external source and the blockchain. Sether moves, monitors and analyses social media data for the blockchain, automating integration with social networks.  What businesses can do with SETHER ? Customer Loyalty Customer Targeting and Guaranteed Promotions Marketing Campaigns Bounty Campaigns Transparent political support Incentivize good PR Proof of Action Develop applications ...and more   Our commitment to SETHER We are building Sether because we need it; this is how it came to be. That is the reason why we are committed to go live regardless of the outcome of the ICO campaign. Hence, there will be no soft-cap, because the project will continue and will go in production.  Stay tuned for  development news and opportunities, by  following and subscribing to our channels on Facebook, Twitter, Linked in and Youtube.  Pre-ICO Begins December 4th  The minimum contribution for pre-ICO: Minimum 0.1 ETH or BTC equivalent with a bonus of 40%  For information on the terms of the pre-sale please contact investor@sether.io or register on the website to get updates.  Whitelist registration is open! Please register on our website.  More details on sether.io  YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC5yq2RFc-BOovbPkv65L-sg Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/setherplatform/ Twitter: https://twitter.com/setherplatform Telegram: https://t.me/setherplatform GitHub: https://github.com/mware-solutions  Press releases  https://cointelegraph.com/press-releases/social-network-automation-for-blockchain-developers https://medium.com/@contact_47998/question-whats-holding-back-smart-blockchain-developers-31e10b0c97aa https://medium.com/@contact_47998/sether-the-new-smart-contract-developer-tool-to-harness-the-power-of-social-media-5ea562b76709 https://medium.com/@contact_47998/whos-afraid-of-social-networks-c299a5a69e3  Stay tuned for more updates

Author: TheShiveringGamer
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: From my understanding of the white paper, there will be three types of nodes: COLLECTION, ANALYSIS and ROUTERS. Are these going to be connected to the ethereum net ? how will it work ?

Author: setherplatform
Title: SETHER - Arbitrating Advertising
Body: Hi !  ONLY the ROUTER nodes will be connected to the Ethereum network. They will reveice events from the Sether smart contract and will orchestrate the other two types of nodes. COLLECTION nodes will be connected to the internet and will download social network data. ANALYSIS nodes will be isolated nodes (no internet connection, no connection to the blockchain net). Their only role is to analyze data in-memory.  Sether
